shared_text:
Carey Kersey
21 hrs ·

CHS Junior Class-Scratch Cupcake Fundraiser

Scratch Cupcakes are AWESOME!! Buy some for yourselves or for a gift. Have a birthday or anniversary coming up? They are perfect for all occasions.

Due to COVID, kids going door to door to sell anything is being discouraged. However, we'd still like to see a great response for this Junior class After Prom fundraiser.

Please reach out to a Junior class kid or Junior parent if you are interested in ordering. Contact Jennifer White-Jorgensen or Ann Polking Vincent if you have any questions. Kids will be selling until October 2. With delivery on October 23rd. Make checks payable to the CHS After-Prom.

Thanks for supporting the Junior Class After-Prom!

post_text: Great job!
shared_text:
Kuemper Catholic Cross Country
September 3 at 9:59 PM ·

Great night for Kuemper runners at WCV! Boys place 1st out of 9 teams and the girls finished 3rd out of 9 teams Medalist for Kuemper was Michael Pottebaum 3rd, Kaleb Booth 7th, Jacob Greving 9th, Patrick Hensel 12th. The Girls were lead by Marie Dea 5th Keziah Janssen 16th and Siena Argarin 22th. Boys had 8 out of 10 runners improve their time from last year's meet. Great job by Ryan North and Victor Esquivel pushing each other at the end to give us a 2 point victory. Also another gutsy run by Alexandria Klein and Lydia Meiners pushing each other to finish so the girls had a team score. It would have been very easy for them to stop. Also, Callie Ferending has been a very consistent runner for us.

post_text:
A message from Elementary Principal, Mr. Rabbitt

Hello Tiger Family,
With many other schools only seeing their students a few times a week and others completely remote, we are grateful that we have the opportunity to have the students back in our buildings learning face to face.
I want to thank you for the patience you have shown during the beginning of this school year as we try to figure things out on a daily basis.

If you had the view that I have, you would see the love for children the CCSD staff at Adams and Fairview Elementary have as they have been working so tightly together, our children have been under constant supervision and support as they have returned to learning.

My team has listened to your feedback, suggestions and recommendations in the past couple weeks and we will be making a couple tweaks to the parent pick up lines to try and smooth out the process.

Remember ~ PICTURES ON TUESDAY and have a safe Labor Day weekend.

Patrick Rabbitt

post_text: Congratulations to our Cross Country runners!
shared_text:
Kuemper Catholic Cross Country
September 1 at 11:04 PM ·

Congratulations to the Knight runners for your performance at DCG
Michael Pottebaum lead the way for the boys to place 16th overall.
Congratulations to runners to newcomers Kaleb Booth, Jacob Greving Victor Esquivel and Ryan North for running your first meet and making it in our top seven runners. We also had Patrick Hensel and Carter Drake making it in our top seven runners.
We had multiple runners run their personal best around 10 for the boys. Special congratulations to Seniors Max Meyers, Grant Neilson and Mitchel Badding for running a personal best.
On the girl's side we had Freshman Marie Dea leading the way running a 21:56 in her first 5K. Also, Siena Argarin was our second runner and Keziah Jannsen ran third. Freshman Callie Ferneding and Kaisen Stypa ran the first 5K meet with Lydia Meiners other varsity runner. We had 2 girls that dropped out in Macy Tiefenthaler and Alexandria Klein and should be back for our next meet. Really gutsy girls!
I think all the girls ran PR today! Great Job!!

post_text: Go Tigers!!
shared_text:
Carroll Tiger Volleyball
August 30 at 9:08 PM ·

Yesterday was our season opener at the Bondurant-Farrar tournament. It was an extremely competitive tournament with 4/6 opponents being preseason ranked and most having a strong tradition of excellence. We went 3-3 on the day with victories over Perry, Pella Christian, and Bondurant-Farrar and close losses to Gilbert, Pella, and Holy Trinity Catholic. I am proud of our growth and competitiveness, but we are hungry for more! Can't wait for our HOME conference opener Tuesday night against Gilbert!

As the new school year begins, Carroll Community School District (K-12) will be using the platform Google Classroom as a way to distribute and organize instructional content between students and teachers. Once school begins, parents/guardians will be invited by the student’s teacher to view daily or weekly progress on your student. Once accepted, you will be receiving email notifications with your student’s class announcements, upcoming assignments, and missing work.

To stay informed of what is happening in your student’s classroom (K-12), we strongly encourage parents/guardians to “Accept” the Google Classroom invitation.

Video tutorials for students/parents regarding Google Classroom, please visit bit.ly/ClassroomCCSD

post_text:
Little Tiger Preschool Announcement

Class Lists:
Class lists are being developed for our preschool program. We ask that parents fill out the transportation request on our school website as soon as possible to make this process cleaner. Parents will be notified in the middle of next week by their classroom teacher.
** It would help to fill it out whether transportation is a yes or a no.

School Start dates:
School Start date is August 31st.

Supplies:
We will not be sharing supplies as we have in the past. We will abide by recommended guidelines for our classrooms taking every effort to keep the environment as safe as possible for staff and students.

Parent Drop Off & Pick Up:
Drop off will once again be on the west side of the building.
Due to busing changes, the number of vehicles this year will be increased and we are asking parents to remain in their car and allow school staff to assist your child to the classroom. Preschool staff will be wearing orange safety vests so children will know who to walk with.

text:
Good afternoon. Below is a link to a transportation form that we need all families to fill out. As you may know, we are trying to finalize our plan for transportation this year and we need to get a count so we can determine how many kids we need to transport. If you are able to transport your student this year, we ask that you do that. We know that it will not be possible for some families to transport their children and we want to provide transportation for those situations. If you have questions call the district office, 712-792-8001 or the transportation office at 712-792-8050. Thank you!

NEW TO THE DISTRICT ONLINE REGISTRATION PROCESS

Welcome! If you are NEW to the Carroll Community School District you will need to enroll in our system. Also, preschool students attending Holy Spirit Center will also need to be registered online.

You may watch the video attached and follow these written instructions from our website to assist you with the process: https://www.carroll.k12.ia.us/parents/new-student-registration/

**If you currently have existing students attending CCSD and need to add a new student within your family, please view the separate post about Current Student Registration.**

post_text:
ONLINE REGISTRATION IS OPEN for CURRENT STUDENTS at CCSD

All CURRENT student(s) in the Carroll Community School District and also 9-12th grade students enrolled at Ar-We-Va taking classes at CCSD will need to complete the registration process. Preschool students need to be registered online as well. Attending preschool open house in the Spring does not mean you are officially registered.

You may watch the video attached to this post and follow these written instructions on the school website https://www.carroll.k12.ia.us/parents/current-student-registration/ to assist you with the process.

**Please note if students are not registered for school they will not have access to use our school internet network and Chromebooks as there is a permission form to complete within the online registration.**

post_text:
The Carroll Community School District is beginning a before and after school program, TigerZone, at Fairview Elementary School this fall for students who are in kindergarten through fourth grade. TigerZone will be open full days during professional development on Thursday, August 20, Friday, August 21, and Monday, August 24. The first day of school is scheduled for Tuesday, August 25. Before and after school care will be available beginning that day. Students can also attend during professional development days throughout the school year.

Please visit bit.ly/TigerZone to learn more and complete the survey in the comments if you are interested in having your child or children participate in the TigerZone Before and Afterschool Program.

Feel free to contact Mary Kohorst, at CCSD District Office, 712-792-8001 or email mkohorst@carrolltigers.org if you have any questions.

Help spread the word and like and share our post!

Summer Meals Program Carroll, Iowa
June 25 at 5:00 PM ·

July Menus + Grab N' Go sign up links..... 5 more weeks.... no meals in August so the staff can have three weeks off before school starts on August 25th. Please share and remind families to get signed up.... Any family with children 0-18 can participate from ANY community... this is not just a Carroll schools program... Mondays = 2 days of meals, Wednesdays = 3 days of meals... pick up from 11-12:30 (Noon - 12:30 is the fastest time)... buzz in line, grab meals and go. It is so easy...

post_text:
Congratulations to Ashley Onken and Luke Woosley on being nominated by the varsity coaches for the senior scholar/athlete award. Individuals who have demonstrated outstanding achievement in varsity sports while maintaining at least a "B" average are eligible for this award. Ashley participated in basketball, track, and softball. Luke participated in football, wrestling, track, and baseball.

Luke also was nominated for the Bernie Saggau award as well. The Bernie Saggau award is presented to a graduating senior who best exemplifies a patriotic spirit; strong religious and moral convictions; honesty, integrity and sportsmanship; who believes games and life should be conducted by the rules.

Shirt and door prize pick up will be THURSDAY, MAY 21 at the high school parking lot between 6-8 pm.

Please follow these guidelines:

1. No one gets out of the car. We will come to you to hand you your items.

3. If possible please have your first & last name printed on paper so we can respond to you quicker.
4. If you can not make this time work please make arrangements for someone to pick up for you.

If you have any questions, please contact Jen Sibenaller!

We have something really fun planned for Friday night at 7:30PM! We are going to play our first ever virtual -- LIVE -- "Tiger Family Feud!" Wrestling Coach Eric Nagl and his family will take on Girls Track Coach Kirk Christensen and his family!
**
WE NEED YOUR HELP to make this work! We are looking for 100 Tiger fans to help us get ready for Friday by answering the questions we will ask during the show. Your answers will give us our top ranked answers for each question!
**
SO, if you would like to help us out, comment with your name below and I will send you a short survey through Facebook Messenger to fill out. (It will take you less than 5 minutes!) But, you have to promise not to share any of the questions with anyone from the Nagl or Christensen families! 😀
**
Stay tuned this week to see who will be playing for each family! You're not going to want to miss this on Friday so mark your calendars now!

text: LIVE with a Tiger: Baking PB Bars

post_text:
Remember, LIVE with a Tiger today at 2:00! Keaton Schoenfeld will be teaching us how to make PB bars! If you want to follow along with us you will need the following ingredients!

1 ½ C Margarine
1 ½ C Creamy Peanut Butter
1 ½ C Sugar
1 ½ C Brown Sugar
2 Eggs
1 TBSP Vanilla
2 tsp Baking Soda
1 tsp Salt
3 C Flour
2 ½ C Oatmeal
1 ⅛ C Chocolate Chips
Frosting:
1 ½ C Powdered Sugar
½ C Creamy Peanut Butter
½ C Milk

Parents, are your students joining in on Google Meet to see their teacher and classmates? Here is a video tutorial that will show you how to install and use Google Meet Grid View extension that will allow you to see your ENTIRE class on your screen, and not just a few people.

CCSD 5th-12th grade students already have this extension installed on their school-issued Chromebooks, but just need to activate the button every time they join in a Google Meet.

Any questions about Google Meet, please contact District Technology Integrationist, Kelli Schulz at kschulz@carrolltigers.org

post_text: SPRING CLOTHING ORDER UPDATE!
shared_text:
Tiger Vision Shop
April 18 at 2:06 PM ·

Spring Clothing Order Update! We are so sad that spring sports have been canceled for the 2020 season! 😭 We never in a million years thought this would happen! We also never thought school would be canceled for the remainder of the year, making it difficult to get your items out to you that have been at the school.
***
With the announcement of the extended school closure, I was able to get to the school and get the items. After sorting everything this morning, (see pictures) items are ready to get out to all of you. We will be having a DRIVE THROUGH pick-up on Tuesday, April 21st from 11:00-1:00 in the high school parking lot.
***
Please enter the U drive on the far north end and drive through the line. Tell us your last name and we will hand your bag to you through your passenger front seat. Thank you and Go Tigers!

post_text: Scrolling through social media and seeing so many of our teachers and coaches expressing their sadness about the extended school closure. Even though we all understand that the safety of our students, staff and community is the most important, it really does break our hearts to not get to see your children everyday! ❤️ Tiger Vision is going to do everything we can to make this time special for all of you who are missing out on the "normal" activities we all love so much. ⛳️⚽️🏅🎓🎭🎨🎼🎷 As our video showed earlier this week, there will be "Better Days" ahead! Tell us what you're missing the most about school/sports/activities and we'll do what we can to help! Maybe we will share a picture, maybe a video, maybe a memorable stat, maybe a LIVE, but something!! We're all in this together, and together we are TIGER STRONG!

post_text:
We have something fun planned for tonight! We will be bringing you the first ever "LIVE with a Tiger." Join us right here on Facebook when we go LIVE at 8:00pm. Tiger Vision Instructor, Chelsea Bissen will be going live with CCSD Technology Integrationist, Kelli Schulz to create flowers made from construction paper! 💐Below is the list of supplies you will need if you want to make flowers with us! Otherwise, just jump on and watch us do our best to be crafty!
***
Supplies:
-Construction paper or colored paper
-Scissors
-Glue
-Circular object to trace about the size of a DVD
-Pencil
***
If you can't join at 8:00pm, it will be recorded for you to watch at a later time. Can't wait to see you!

post_text:
CHS and CMS Students can pick up their Chromebooks if they left them at school at the following times tomorrow.

Wednesday, April 8th
Chromebook Pick Up at CMS from 11am-1pm
Chromebook Pick Up at CHS from 2pm-4pm

The student and/or guardian will ring in at the front door and state their name and grade. A member of the tech dept will then go and get the device and hand it out the front door. At CHS, a custodian will be required from 2pm-4pm to access any lockers that the devices may be in.

Chromebook Repair/Replace Times:
Tuesdays and Thursdays from 11am-1pm ONLY AT CHS.

The student and/or guardian will ring in at the front door of CHS and locker number (if the device is in their locker). A member of the tech dept will collect the defective device at the door and hand out the replacement device. Make sure you bring the device AND charger when you drop off your chromebook for repair.

E-mail Craig Rowedder with questions. crowedder@carrolltigers.org

post_text:
IMPORTANT GRAB AND GO MEALS ANNOUNCEMENT:
For the safety of our staff preparing and distributing the Grab and Go meals, starting on Monday, April 6th please DO NOT have anyone sitting in the front passenger seat of your vehicle. The staff will drop your bags right inside your open window, side door, or tailgate. The governor is really pushing for people to stay home, so please don't bring extra people in your vehicle unless you absolutely need to. With this we are trying to minimize the amount of contact our staff has with the public. If you are needing to open your side door, please pull all the way up to the final orange cone, put your vehicle in park and be ready for a staff member to quickly put the meals in your car so they can move onto the next. This will help speed up the pickup process. Thank you.

post_text:
Don’t forget the rules for the parade starting at 6:15 tonight!!

1. School staff can’t stop and talk. We can wave 👋 and honk our horns!!
-
2. NO ONE can approach the cars 🚗....you can stand on your porch 🏠, in your yard, or in your driveway and wave 👋 to your Carroll Community School and Kuemper Catholic School staff.
-
3. Do NOT meet as a group or stand together; keep to your own property to watch the parade. Remember to practice safe social distancing.
-
Also, students and community members - make a sign, then be sure to listen for horns - Run outside and wave.👋 We, the staff of all schools, are looking forward to the excitement from all of you, too!
-
***This is not a school/district sponsored event or activity; this is organized by a group of individuals who work together for the sake of our students and community.***

post_text: Hello from the Conley residence, home of Mrs. Conley! We are keeping ourselves busy each day, but it has been an adjustment. We have three boys: Dylan (5), Colten (3), and Jace (1). The older boys have learned that work comes before play. We work on school activities in the morning for about an hour, then we move to Legos, trains, or other toys. The afternoons can be spent on baking, playing outside, playing the iPad, participating in Read Alouds with Diane, and reading books on Scholastic Learn at Home. The older two have grown up quite a bit during this time; taking on the chores of unloading the dishwasher and helping clean up our large yard (without complaining...so far)! Jace enjoys time with me, playing in his room, stealing his brothers’ things, taking afternoon naps, and playing outside. I know all of the teachers miss everyone. Stay safe and we are thinking of you!

UPDATE: PLEASE READ ALL DIRECTIONS BEFORE POSTING (We only post the new team total, not the number of miles you walked/ran/biked)
*********
We know there's not a lot we can do these days, but staying active is something that hasn't been canceled! Today we are going to start 🐯"Tigers Go The Extra Mile"🐯 where we are going to count how many miles Tigers can get in collectively during our time away from school!
--
This challenge is for ANY Tiger or Tiger fan, and can be walking, running, jogging, or biking so if your family of 4 goes on a 1 mile walk, that will count as 4 miles!
**********
DIRECTIONS:
You will add your miles to the bottom comment and comment with our new team total. For example, if the last comment says 27 and you walked 2 miles, you will comment with the number 29. ‼️ Please follow CDC guidelines and walk by yourself or with your immediate family, thank you!
**********
Can't wait to see how high our number can get!

post_text:
Let's all take some time to say thank you to our essential workers! Whether that be doctors and nurses, truckers, grocery store workers, etc, we want to say thank you!! It doesn't matter if they work in Carroll or not, if they are a Carroll Tiger fan, we want to be able to say thank you!!
**Tag us in your "thank you" post (remember to make it public so we can share) or comment on this post with their picture, name, and position so we can all say thank you!
**We want to start by thanking CHS grad, Tyler Jensen, who is a Flight Nurse, LifeGuard Air Ambulance at St. Luke's Hospital in Cedar Rapids and an ED Nurse and House Supervisor at Allen Hospital in Waterloo, Iowa! Join me in thanking him for all he's doing to keep Iowan's healthy and safe!

post_text:
Read this awesome update from Señora Fish and join me in congratulating her!
---
"My family grew by one last week with the addition of baby Chase. While my daughter, Beth, and her husband were at the hospital with grandson #1, we enjoyed time with our 3-year-old granddaughter, Cami, and 100-pound “grandpuppy”, Essie. No visitors were allowed—not even little sisters, so we made other plans: Built Lego castles, put together puzzles and colored. (No Spanish lessons, but Cami still thinks I say some weird things!) One rainy day we washed a bucket of golf balls--in a bubble bath, of course. When it was nice outside, we took some long walks. This one was at Swan Lake. The girls took the lead with my husband."

Irlbeck Precision is looking for someone that might be interested in working for them at the end of the day (8th period and/or Advisory) and after school. They are looking for someone who is possibly interested in employment with them after high school. If interested call 775-2275.

JOB DESCRIPTION FOR SHOP ASSISTANT: This self-motivated individual will be buffing, polishing and using hand tools and must be a team player, reliable, trustworthy, and hardworking with a passion for learning new skills. Must be able to perform the physical requirements of the position such as heavy lifting, standing, repetitive motions, pushing, pulling, and using powered equipment. Attention to detail is required. This individual also must take instruction well and be a willing and quick learner. The ability to read a tape measure, understand units of measurement and transfer measurements is mandatory.

post_text:
Tiger Vision students, Ben Sampson, Markie Madsen, Drew Munson and Isaac Lo, had a really cool experience this afternoon when they got to meet Jeffrey Morris, writer, director and production designer for the forth-coming films Persephone and Oceanus as well as the animated series Parallel man.

We enjoyed hearing him speak about who and what influenced him and how he got his start in filmmaking. He told us having the courage to make one phone call to Don Fraser, the mayor of Minneapolis, MN as well as Don taking a chance on him and helping him meet people all lead him to where he is today. Thank you Joel Lundstrom and DMACC for the invite, we really enjoyed it! Hoping to take a class trip to Persephone when it comes out in theaters in 2021!

post_text: The 8th grade Family Consumer Science students have been working on a very unique sewing project this year where they sew "Little Monsters" to give to the kindergarteners. post_text: Excellence comes in all shapes, sizes & languages! Today Señora Lee caught excellence 9th hour when Soleil Basurco and Nathan Shoesmith volunteered their time to help students make up participation points in Spanish! Señora Lee says "these two are excellent Spanish students and are always volunteering to assist others." Great job Soleil and Nathan! #catchingexcellence #On4Carroll
